  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA1-kiḷavi">itu pirivuṇarttiya tōḻikkut talaivi colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said to the confidante who had
          announced separation.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA1">
          <l>niṉṟa collar nīṭutōṉ ṟiṉiya</l>
          <l>reṉṟu meṉṟōḷ piripaṟi yalarē</l>
          <l>tāmarait taṇṭā tūti mīmicaic</l>
          <l>cāntiṟ ṟoṭutta tīntēṉ pōlap</l>
          <l>puraiya maṉṟa puraiyōr kēṇmai</l>
          <l>nīriṉ ṟamaiyā vulakam pōlat</l>
          <l>tammiṉ ṟamaiyā nannayan taruḷi</l>
          <l>naṟunutal pacatta lañcic</l>
          <l>ciṟumai yuṟupavō ceypaṟi yalarē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l rend="indent">He who is constant in speaking,</l>
          <l rend="indent">who is pleasing apparently a long time,</l>
          <l>he will never know of separating from my shoulder.</l>
          <l rend="indent">Like the sweet honey stored in the sandal tree</l>
          <l rend="indent">on the height1, after [bees] have filled themselves</l>
          <l rend="indent">with the cool pollen of the day lotus,</l>
          <l>great, certainly, are<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">puraiya</term>, the predicate, is n.pl., which means
            that also <term xml:lang="ta">kēṇmai</term> has to be read as a pl. Perhaps the point is to make a general
            statement.</note> the friendships of great people.</l>
          <l rend="indent">Since [he] is considerate,</l>
          <l rend="indent">longing for us who are not content without him,</l>
          <l rend="indent">as the world is not content without water,</l>
          <l rend="indent">since [he] fears [our] fragrant forehead turning pale,</l>
          <l>will he have baseness? He won't know of [such] doing.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
